INSERT INTO contract_templates (contract_type, jurisdiction, version, title, preamble, recitals, clauses, signature_block, placeholders, is_active, metadata) VALUES (
  'safe_note',
  'us_texas',
  1,
  'Simple Agreement for Future Equity - SAFE (Texas)',
  'This Simple Agreement for Future Equity (the "SAFE") is entered into as of {{effective_date}} (the "Effective Date"), by and between {{party_a_company}}, a Texas {{entity_type}} (the "Company"), and {{party_b_name}} (the "Investor").',
  'WHEREAS, the Company is raising capital to fund its business operations and growth;
WHEREAS, the Investor wishes to provide capital to the Company in exchange for the right to receive equity in the Company upon occurrence of certain events;
NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, the parties agree as follows:',
  '[{"id":"definitions","title":"1. DEFINITIONS","content":"1.1 \"Purchase Amount\" means {{investment_amount}}, the amount paid by the Investor to the Company under this SAFE.\n\n1.2 \"Equity Financing\" means a bona fide transaction or series of transactions in which the Company issues and sells shares of Preferred Stock for the purpose of raising capital, with total proceeds (excluding any SAFE conversions) of not less than {{qualifying_round_threshold}}.\n\n1.3 \"Discount Rate\" means {{discount_rate}}%, representing the discount applied to the price per share in an Equity Financing.\n\n1.4 \"Valuation Cap\" means {{valuation_cap}}, the maximum company valuation used to calculate the conversion price.\n\n1.5 \"Liquidity Event\" means: (a) a Change of Control; or (b) an Initial Public Offering.\n\n1.6 \"Change of Control\" means: (a) a sale, transfer, or disposition of all or substantially all of the Company''s assets; (b) a consolidation, merger, or similar transaction where the Company''s stockholders immediately prior to such transaction own less than 50% of the surviving entity; or (c) the transfer of more than 50% of the Company''s voting power.\n\n1.7 \"Initial Public Offering\" or \"IPO\" means the closing of the Company''s first firm-commitment underwritten initial public offering of Common Stock.\n\n1.8 \"Dissolution Event\" means: (a) a voluntary termination of operations; (b) a general assignment for the benefit of creditors; or (c) any other liquidation, dissolution, or winding up of the Company.\n\n1.9 \"SAFE Preferred Stock\" means shares of a series of Preferred Stock issued to the Investor upon conversion of this SAFE, having identical rights, privileges, and restrictions as the shares issued in the Equity Financing, except for: (a) the per share liquidation preference and any dividend rate, which shall equal the SAFE Price; and (b) the basis for any price-based anti-dilution protection.","type":"standard","order":1},{"id":"investment","title":"2. INVESTMENT","content":"2.1 Investment. In exchange for the Purchase Amount, the Company hereby issues to the Investor the right to receive shares of the Company''s Capital Stock, subject to the terms set forth herein.\n\n2.2 Payment. The Investor shall pay the Purchase Amount to the Company within 5 business days of the Effective Date by wire transfer or check to an account designated by the Company.\n\n2.3 No Interest. The Purchase Amount shall not accrue or bear interest.\n\n2.4 Use of Funds. The Company shall use the Purchase Amount for general working capital and business purposes.","type":"standard","order":2},{"id":"conversion","title":"3. CONVERSION EVENTS","content":"3.1 Equity Financing. Upon the closing of an Equity Financing, the Purchase Amount shall automatically convert into shares of SAFE Preferred Stock at a price per share equal to the lesser of: (a) the price per share paid by investors in the Equity Financing multiplied by (1 minus the Discount Rate); or (b) the Valuation Cap divided by the Company Capitalization immediately prior to the Equity Financing (the \"SAFE Price\").\n\n3.2 Liquidity Event. If a Liquidity Event occurs before the conversion of this SAFE, the Investor may elect, at the Investor''s option, to either: (a) receive a cash payment equal to the Purchase Amount; or (b) convert the Purchase Amount into shares of Common Stock at a price per share equal to the Valuation Cap divided by the Company Capitalization immediately prior to the Liquidity Event, and participate in the Liquidity Event on the same terms as other common stockholders.\n\n3.3 Dissolution Event. If a Dissolution Event occurs before the conversion of this SAFE, the Company shall pay to the Investor an amount equal to the Purchase Amount, subject to the rights and preferences of any holders of Preferred Stock.\n\n3.4 Company Capitalization. \"Company Capitalization\" means the sum of: (a) all shares of Capital Stock issued and outstanding; (b) all shares reserved under any equity incentive plan; and (c) all shares reserved for issuance under any convertible securities, in each case immediately prior to the applicable event, excluding shares issuable upon conversion of this SAFE and any other SAFEs.","type":"standard","order":3},{"id":"investor_rights","title":"4. INVESTOR RIGHTS","content":"4.1 Information Rights. Until conversion, the Company shall provide the Investor with: (a) annual financial statements within 120 days after each fiscal year end; and (b) notice of any Equity Financing, Liquidity Event, or Dissolution Event at least 5 days prior to closing.\n\n4.2 Pro-Rata Rights. If this SAFE converts in an Equity Financing, the Investor shall have the right to participate in such Equity Financing on the same terms as other investors, up to an amount necessary to maintain the Investor''s pro-rata ownership percentage.\n\n4.3 No Voting Rights. This SAFE does not entitle the Investor to any voting rights prior to conversion.\n\n4.4 MFN Provision. If the Company issues any other SAFEs with more favorable terms (including a higher valuation cap or greater discount), the Investor may elect to have the terms of this SAFE amended to match such more favorable terms.","type":"standard","order":4},{"id":"company_representations","title":"5. COMPANY REPRESENTATIONS AND COVENANTS","content":"5.1 Organization. The Company is duly organized, validly existing, and in good standing under the laws of the State of Texas.\n\n5.2 Authorization. The Company has all necessary power and authority to execute and deliver this SAFE and to perform its obligations hereunder.\n\n5.3 Valid Issuance. The shares issued upon conversion of this SAFE will be validly issued, fully paid, and non-assessable.\n\n5.4 No Conflict. The execution and performance of this SAFE does not violate or conflict with any law, the Company''s organizational documents, or any material agreement to which the Company is a party.\n\n5.5 Use of Funds. The Company shall use the Purchase Amount for general working capital and business purposes.\n\n5.6 Maintenance of Status. The Company shall maintain its corporate existence in good standing under Texas law.","type":"standard","order":5},{"id":"investor_representations","title":"6. INVESTOR REPRESENTATIONS","content":"6.1 Authorization. The Investor has all necessary power and authority to execute and deliver this SAFE.\n\n6.2 Accredited Investor. The Investor is an \"accredited investor\" as defined in Rule 501 of Regulation D promulgated under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended.\n\n6.3 Investment Intent. The Investor is acquiring this SAFE and any shares issued upon conversion for investment purposes only and not with a view to distribution or resale.\n\n6.4 Sophistication. The Investor has sufficient knowledge and experience in financial and business matters to evaluate the risks and merits of this investment.\n\n6.5 Risk Acknowledgment. The Investor understands that this investment involves substantial risk and that the Investor may lose the entire Purchase Amount.\n\n6.6 No Reliance. The Investor is not relying on any advice from the Company or its representatives regarding tax, legal, or investment matters.","type":"standard","order":6},{"id":"miscellaneous","title":"7. MISCELLANEOUS","content":"7.1 Governing Law. This SAFE shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Texas, without regard to conflict of laws principles.\n\n7.2 Venue. Any dispute arising out of or relating to this SAFE shall be resolved in the state or federal courts located in {{venue_county}} County, Texas.\n\n7.3 Amendment. This SAFE may only be amended with the written consent of both parties.\n\n7.4 Assignment. The Investor may not assign this SAFE without the Company''s prior written consent, except to an affiliate or in connection with a transfer for estate planning purposes.\n\n7.5 Notices. All notices shall be in writing and delivered to the addresses set forth herein, or to such other address as either party may designate.\n\n7.6 Entire Agreement. This SAFE constitutes the entire agreement between the parties regarding its subject matter and supersedes all prior agreements and understandings.\n\n7.7 Severability. If any provision of this SAFE is held to be invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall remain in full force and effect.\n\n7.8 Counterparts. This SAFE may be executed in counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an original.\n\n7.9 Electronic Signatures. Signatures transmitted electronically shall be deemed original signatures and shall be enforceable under the Texas Uniform Electronic Transactions Act (Texas Business and Commerce Code, Chapter 322).\n\n7.10 No Employment Relationship. Nothing in this SAFE shall be construed to create an employment, partnership, or joint venture relationship between the parties.\n\n7.11 Securities Law Compliance. The issuance of this SAFE and any shares upon conversion is intended to be exempt from registration under federal and state securities laws. The Company and Investor agree to cooperate in taking any actions necessary to comply with applicable securities laws.","type":"standard","order":7}]'::jsonb,
  'IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this SAFE as of {{signature_date}}.

COMPANY:
